================================================================================
VOICEVOX (Text-to-Speech Engine)
================================================================================

This application uses the VOICEVOX text-to-speech engine to synthesize
speech. The engine is invoked at runtime via Docker; no VOICEVOX source
code is bundled with this distribution.

  - Project:       https://voicevox.hiroshiba.jp/
  - Engine source: https://github.com/VOICEVOX/voicevox_engine
  - Copyright:     (c) Hiroshiba Kazuyuki
  - License:       GNU Lesser General Public License v3
                   (or alternative commercial license; see project page)
  - Terms of use:  https://voicevox.hiroshiba.jp/term/

Per the VOICEVOX Software Terms of Use, the following credit is provided:
"Powered by VOICEVOX". The full credit is also displayed in the
application's footer (see "Credits / License" section).

================================================================================
VOICEVOX Characters (Tohoku Zunko / Zundamon Project)
================================================================================

The following character voices may be used by this application to
synthesize speech for narration:

  - VOICEVOX:四国めたん (default)
  - VOICEVOX:ずんだもん

These characters are part of the ずんずんPJ (Tohoku Zunko / Zundamon
Project) operated by SSS LLC. They are subject to the project's Voice
Source Usage Terms (音源利用規約) and Character Usage Guidelines
(キャラクター利用の手引き):

  - Voice Source Usage Terms:    https://zunko.jp/con_ongen_kiyaku.html
  - Character Usage Guidelines: https://zunko.jp/guideline.html

The voice source terms require a "VOICEVOX:" prefixed credit for each
character whose voice is used. The required credit labels are
reproduced in the application's footer.

This project is non-commercial and open source. Under the project's
guidelines, no prior application is required for non-commercial voice
synthesis use.

